# Installation Guide

## Step 1 – Update Ubuntu Server

```
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

---

## Step 2 – Download Wazuh Installation Script

```
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.7/wazuh-install.sh
```

---

## Step 3 – Install Wazuh Platform

```
sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a
```

This command installs:

• Wazuh Manager
• Wazuh Dashboard
• Wazuh Indexer
• Filebeat

---

## Step 4 – Verify Services

```
sudo systemctl status wazuh-manager
sudo systemctl status wazuh-indexer
sudo systemctl status wazuh-dashboard
```

Expected output:

```
active (running)
```

---

# Agent Installation (Ubuntu Desktop)

## Download Wazuh Agent

```
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/wazuh-agent_4.7.5-1_amd64.deb
```

---

## Install Agent

```
sudo WAZUH_MANAGER='192.168.64.3' dpkg -i wazuh-agent_4.7.5-1_amd64.deb
```

---

## Enable and Start Agent

```
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable wazuh-agent
sudo systemctl start wazuh-agent
```

---

## Verify Agent Status

```
sudo systemctl status wazuh-agent
```

Expected output:

```
Active: active (running)
```

---

# Verify Agent Connection

Run on the Wazuh server:

```
sudo /var/ossec/bin/agent_control -l
```

Example output:

```
ID: 001
Name: ubuntu-desktop
IP: 192.168.64.20
Status: Active
```

