# Attack Simulation

To verify the SOC detection capability, a file modification test was performed.

## File Integrity Monitoring Test

```
sudo nano /etc/passwd
```

This simulates unauthorized modification of a critical system file.

The Wazuh agent detects the change and generates a security alert.

---

# Security Alert Example

```
Rule ID: 554
Level: 7
Description: File '/etc/passwd' modified
Agent: ubuntu-desktop
```

This alert indicates a modification to a sensitive system file.

